general_inquiry.response:
The Jacobian matrix of the vector-valued function \(\begin{pmatrix} f(x,y,z)\\ g(x,y,z) \\ h(x,y,z)\end{pmatrix}\) where \(f(x,y,z) = \cos(x)\), \(g(x,y,z) = z\), and \(h(x,y,z) = \sqrt[3]{z}\) is:

\[
\begin{pmatrix}
-\sin(x) & 0 & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 1 \\
0 & 0 & \frac{1}{3}z^{-\frac{2}{3}}
\end{pmatrix}
\]
